# Claude Code Rules for CropForecaster

## Project Context
This is CropForecaster - an operational weather monitoring system for Australian wheat crop risk assessment. Focus on production reliability over research exploration.

## Key Documentation to Reference
- `docs/silo_api_usage_guide.md` - SILO API integration patterns
- `prd.md` - Event detection thresholds and MVP requirements  
- `task_manager.md` - Current sprint priorities and blockers
- `CLAUDE.md` - System architecture and specialized agent scopes

## Development Priorities (September 2025)
1. M1 Sprint (Sep 10): Basic frost/heat detection working
2. API reliability and error handling critical
3. CSV output format must match external system requirements
4. Performance target: <10 seconds for 2000+ stations

## Code Standards
- Production-ready error handling required
- Comprehensive logging for operational monitoring
- API rate limiting respect (1-2 req/sec max)
- Data validation for all weather inputs

## When to Use Specialized Agents
- silo-api-specialist: For all SILO API integration work
- event-detection-developer: For threshold logic and validation
- csv-export-system: For output formatting and data exports